          while others manage longer intervals comfortably. It's crucial to
          figure out your puppy’s personal rhythm. Knowing exactly when your
          puppy typically wakes up, naps, or needs to relieve themselves
          helps you provide timely and effective care, reducing accidents
          and stress for both you and your puppy.
        </p>

